PN,31304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1774123873
OL,3,CChelsea Flower Show gnome ban lifted
OL,4,Cto encourage 'curiosity'
OL,6,FThe garden has been designed by
OL,7,Fhorticulturist and TV presenter
OL,8,FFrances Tophill, and features nods to
OL,9,Fits champions, the King, Sir David
OL,10,FBeckham, and Alan Titchmarsh.
OL,12,FOne such nod celebrates a tradition at
OL,13,FHighgrove Gardens, the King's
OL,14,Fresidence in Gloucestershire, where a
OL,15,Fgnome is often to be found in the
OL,16,Fgarden stumpery.
OL,18,FTophill, who is creating her first
OL,19,Fgarden at Chelsea, said she wanted to
OL,20,Fcreate something "very joyful,
OL,21,Fcolourful, fun".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1774123873
OL,3,CChelsea Flower Show gnome ban lifted
OL,4,Cto encourage 'curiosity'
OL,6,F"The idea of this space is about
OL,7,Fencouraging entrance into horticulture
OL,8,Fand rural crafts generally, which is
OL,9,Fsomething that the RHS and the King's
OL,10,FFoundation are obviously passionately
OL,11,Fworking on all the time," she said.
OL,13,FIn the garden, enthusiasts can expect
OL,14,Fto see seven raised beds growing
OL,15,Fvegetables and herbs, referencing Sir
OL,16,FDavid's number 7 shirt.
OL,18,FMs Tophill said the former footballer
OL,19,Fis "a huge veg grower" and she was
OL,20,Ftrying to grow him garlic as one of
OL,21,Fhis favourites.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1774123873
OL,3,CChelsea Flower Show gnome ban lifted
OL,4,Cto encourage 'curiosity'
OL,6,FThere will also be delphiniums, one of
OL,7,Fthe favourite flowers of the King, who
OL,8,Fgrows them prominently at his
OL,9,FHighgrove garden and is patron of the
OL,10,FDelphinium Society, and rose varieties
OL,11,Fnamed after the three champions will
OL,12,Falso be grown in it.
OL,14,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,15,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,16,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,17,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1774123873
OL,3,CChelsea Flower Show gnome ban lifted
OL,4,Cto encourage 'curiosity'
OL,6,FThe garden, which will not be judged,
OL,7,Fwill have an oak building that
OL,8,Frepresents a "museum of curiosities",
OL,9,Fwhich will live on as an outdoor
OL,10,Fclassroom when the garden moves to an
OL,11,Feducational centre after the show.
OL,13,FMs Tophill added that the garden would
OL,14,Fbe free of man-made materials,
OL,15,Fincluding concrete, in recognition of
OL,16,FCharles's focus on sustainability.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/8
